WEBVTT

00:00.800 --> 00:03.394
<i>If you haven 't watched</i> The O.C.,
<i>here's what you've missed.</i>

00:03.560 --> 00:06.154
- I'm not interested in Marissa, all right?
- Then prove it.

00:06.520 --> 00:08.795
Just come down, Johnny, please?

00:09.400 --> 00:11.436
- You're glad he's gone?
- Not gonna answer that.

00:11.600 --> 00:12.919
- What do you want?
- You.

00:13.080 --> 00:14.513
Late night last night?

00:14.680 --> 00:17.069
Boy likes girl. Girl has access
to influential father.

00:17.240 --> 00:18.639
Boy's boss needs to close a deal.

00:18.800 --> 00:19.949
- I'm in.
- You're in?

00:20.120 --> 00:21.553
Caleb would've been proud.

00:21.720 --> 00:23.517
- Where's the line?
- I'm not worried about you...

00:23.680 --> 00:25.033
...knowing where the line is.

00:25.200 --> 00:27.634
Are you a friend of Johnny's?
I'm his cousin, Sadie.

00:27.800 --> 00:30.394
I was wondering if I could
give you a hand.

00:30.560 --> 00:32.073
We got unfinished business.

00:33.640 --> 00:34.834
Come on.

00:39.880 --> 00:41.279
We should take our pants off.

00:42.440 --> 00:44.237
You wouldn't have come
if you didn't want to see me.

00:44.400 --> 00:45.992
- Go away.
- What the hell's he doing here?

00:48.760 --> 00:51.832
<i>Some might say as a teenage girl</i>
<i>growing up in Orange County...</i>

00:52.000 --> 00:53.991
<i>... everything is ours for the taking.</i>

00:54.160 --> 00:55.957
<i>But sooner or later,</i>
<i>we have to choose.</i>

00:59.080 --> 01:01.753
- Hey.
<i>- You don 't choose to choose...</i>

01:01.920 --> 01:03.956
<i>...choosing chooses you.</i>
- Okay, what's that?

01:04.519 --> 01:06.556
<i>And when we choose,</i>
<i>we're left with our ch...</i>

01:07.880 --> 01:10.155
Oh, my God, you're listening
to your own voice.

01:10.320 --> 01:12.880
All the TV shows I watch,
all these women have voiceovers.

01:13.040 --> 01:14.792
They gave one to April on <i>The Valley.</i>

01:14.960 --> 01:17.349
Where most of these voiceovers
don't make much sense...

01:17.520 --> 01:19.875
...they make your life
seem dramatic and meaningful.

01:20.040 --> 01:21.712
Our lives need to be
more dramatic?

01:21.880 --> 01:23.199
No, not yours.

01:23.360 --> 01:26.875
It's our senior year, second semester.
I think things should be more poignant.

01:27.040 --> 01:29.315
- We don't have much time.
- You're right about that.

01:29.480 --> 01:31.471
We don't have much time.
We're late, come on.

01:31.640 --> 01:33.915
- Seth and Ryan are waiting.
- I'll be right there.

01:37.200 --> 01:38.997
<i>No one said choosing would be easy.</i>

01:39.160 --> 01:41.355
<i>But not choosing is even less easy.</i>

01:41.520 --> 01:43.829
<i>Or something.</i>

01:46.160 --> 01:49.118
- So where is Atwood, anyway?
- I don't know, and I don't care.

01:49.280 --> 01:51.077
Yeah, I haven't seen him for a while.

01:51.240 --> 01:53.754
Yeah, but look at it this way:
The hot tub's roomier.

01:53.920 --> 01:56.832
Plus, two girls and a guy.
I like those odds.

01:58.080 --> 02:00.719
You know what? You're right, Cohen.

02:00.880 --> 02:05.556
- Hot tub, house to ourselves...
- I have been kind of Ionely.

02:05.720 --> 02:07.153
And I have kissed a girl before.

02:07.840 --> 02:09.910
And I've always wanted to.

02:10.080 --> 02:12.116
You guys are kidding.

02:12.280 --> 02:14.077
You know what they say, Cohen.

02:14.240 --> 02:17.312
- What happens in the hot tub...
- Stays in the hot tub.

02:17.480 --> 02:20.278
Yeah, you guys are really committed
to this joke. I commend you.

02:20.440 --> 02:22.192
- Who's joking?
- Yeah.

02:22.360 --> 02:24.191
- Cohen, what's the matter?
- Nothing.

02:24.360 --> 02:27.557
- You're not man enough for two girls?
- I gotta call Ryan.

02:30.120 --> 02:32.634
- Be gentle, that pipe is old.
- lf you're such an expert...

02:32.800 --> 02:35.394
...why'd you ask for my help?
- I didn't ask for your help.

02:35.560 --> 02:37.437
- I almost got it. Almost...
- Wait, hold on.

02:37.600 --> 02:40.194
- Not so hard, you're gonna break it.
- It's not gonna break.

02:40.360 --> 02:42.590
- Don't twist so hard. Turn it off!
- I got it.

02:42.760 --> 02:44.830
- Thank you for the help.
- Here's a towel.

02:45.000 --> 02:47.673
Anytime, at your service.
You're too dry, though.

02:47.840 --> 02:49.796
- That's mean.
- You okay?

02:49.960 --> 02:51.234
Fine.

02:51.680 --> 02:53.511
I'll get that. And some towels.

